My favorite features of the GoPro Hero 8 are the Hypersmooth 2.0 and it is  waterproof. The device may be small but its image stabilization technology is really powerful that it can capture image without the need for balancing! Furthermore, i have seen many beautiful underwater shoot with GoPro and I really hope to own one. Cant’t wait for this Covid virus to be gone and we can resume traveling again. Nevertheless, thankful for this circuit breaker, it allows me to slow down my pace and spend more time with my toddler. The most memorable activity I have done with my son during this #circuitbreaker was to bake a Banana Cake! It’s our first bake ever! Though it was messy, but it was quite a rewarding experience! Hope to be the lucky Dad to win this GoPro Hero 8 and start capturing all the moments with my family! 💙💙💙 @luchuan_sim

I would love a GoPro Hero8 to capture my family’s best moments and I am really impressed by the hands-free voice command features, so I can use my GoPro with ease even when my hands are full or dirty from all the playtime and adventures! I love how it is rugged and waterproof as well…it means it’s adventure-proof! One memorable activity I did with my kids was to make and design kites with them. Threw in a lesson on aerodynamics (lift, gravity, drag, etc) and stories on how my own Dad taught me how to fly a kite too, so it was a mixture of art, science and nostalgia! Figured that making kites will be a good idea because we can go fly them in a large, open, field, keep to social distancing guidelines quite easily and get some exercise.  The kids had a blast, and so did I! (Followed both IG accounts; subscribed on youtube and left a comment on your Don Don Donki video; commented, tagged and shared!) @tingaling8888

The most memorable activity during this #CircuitBreaker is when I am able to sit down with my Son (5y.o) and giving him my 100% attention to practice writing his Chinese name. Many would ask why is it so memorable when every other day you could do it with him. 
Without this #CircuitBreaker, we adults are out working and by the time we are back, the little ones are already either asleep or we would be left with little energy to do something with them. Our attention level would definitely be lower then this currenlt moment where many are working from home. 
Given name by the parents is the root to the start of his life. Having 100% attention given to him during the practice, I corrected his technique(笔画) and explained to him the meaning of his name and the root of his family name. Now he would at times proudly tell me papa, I know how to write my name with the correct 笔画 and tell me the steps on writing it. This isn't just a memorable moment that will always stay in my heart, but also a moment as a proud Father that had teach his son the root and meaning of his name.

Does the word “fort” spark memories of secret hideouts you built in your closet or living room? Our childhood forts still evoke powerful memories, though they probably weren’t much to look at or particularly well-constructed. Forts were both sanctuary and home base for our developing imaginations. We built them, we made the rules (including who could enter), and because of that we were the landlords and we were empowered.  Forts also provided comfort—a calm place just for us in the midst of a sometimes chaotic world. Forts provide a much-needed respite—if children get to design and make it themselves. That’s why my husband's most memorable parenting moment during this #CircuitBreaker was when our children and himself created their own Fort —to provide a space and #FunWithinMyFourWalls specifically designed for my children to build the forts of their dreams.
